&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Veo, our mission is to end car dependency by making clean transportation accessible to all. A leading shared micromobility provider in North America, Veo provides millions of bike and scooter rides annually in over 60 cities and universities from Los Angeles to New York City.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Veo offers the most diverse and accessible vehicle fleet in the country built to expand who can ride and what trips are possible. We design and manufacture our vehicles, hardware, and software systems in-house and operate our local markets directly to ensure safe and reliable service. As the first profitable micromobility company in North America, Veo is built for long-term growth and partnership with cities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Veo has been recognized as one of Fast Company’s Most Innovative Companies and a Top GreenTech Company by TIME. As we continue to scale, we are looking for exceptionally talented individuals who are excited to help shape the next era of micromobility.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Technical Supply Chain Manager will serve as the key bridge between Supply Chain, Product, Operations, Quality, and Engineering teams to optimize hardware lifecycle management, vehicle repair and quality, parts consumption and inventory efficiency. This role combines technical hardware expertise with supply chain operations, driving data-driven decisions to improve serviceability, reduce costs, and enhance vehicle reliability across the North American markets. This role will be based in our Santa Monica HQ office four days a week Monday-Thursday.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SKU &amp;amp; Inventory Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead SKU rationalization and simplification initiatives to improve our current process of parts ordering, inventory management, distribution and vehicle maintenance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive initiatives to reduce obsolete, excess, and surplus inventory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and deliver structured SKU management training programs for market teams, covering parts ordering processes, inventory management, and vehicle repair practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parts Consumption &amp;amp; Cost Optimization&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Supply Chain, Product, and Operations teams to analyze parts consumption trends and identify opportunities to reduce SKU burn rates, overall hardware cost and labor cost.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement strategies to improve parts utilization, reduce waste, and increase operational efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor hardware performance metrics and recommend corrective actions based on field data and consumption patterns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hardware Quality &amp;amp; Product Improvement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide hardware performance insights to guide product development, supplier selection, and quality improvement initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze field failures, repair trends, and warranty data to identify root causes and recommend design or supplier improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Engineering, Supply Chain, Operations and Quality teams to improve product reliability and serviceability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary liaison between U.S. operations and Asia-based Quality teams for vehicle quality issues, field feedback, and corrective action implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Operations and Supply Chain teams to improve reverse logistics efficiency and support continuous improvement initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt
